# 2026-04-17-page



## P is for Page

While writing online has its function. Its endless virtual space that can be thought of as pages. They aren't in fact
real pages. At least in the physical state, it is in fact a facsimile. Which had me in thought today, while I was reading,
twelve months, a rather somber book from Jim Butcher. I kept thinking about pages. About how I waited so long to read this
book. That finally I got to once again join a real joy of a book to read, even though this one especially is grieving.

The Dresden Files is alot. A slow accrual of a series. One that over the years ive enjoyed more and more. Page by page.
One that has made me laugh and at other times make me laugh harder. Made me think about buying a vw bug and made me really
think about my own habits. My own tiny world and the things within that I grasp to when everything feels like its changing.

As such I really liked the one aptly named 'Changes', it was probably my favorite in the series. Simply for that sudden, and
hopefully non spoiler, absolute interesting forced life changes that Harry had to go through. It made me think of someone
being pushed out of a plane or moved to Alaska on a bet. It was a fantastic spinning of tables, and some great pages to
read through.

So, as I page through this work, and I think back to the world ive had the privilege of reading in days past. Its nice, and
not without reproach that I say virtual pages are not as impactful as real ones. Surely kindle is just as fine as a library
book. But im just saying, its a vibe and I like reading real books, with real pages, that have good worlds to visit.


